---
title: Incitement to Hatred
author: Huangpan Zhang
layout: post
---

Hate speech detection or offensive language detection are well-established but controversial NLP tasks, the reaction of such content is usually deletion and punishment. However, given the importance of freedom of expression for the public discourse in a democracy, determining statements that would potentially be subject to these measures requires a legal justiﬁcation that outweighs the right to free speech in the respective case

We begin the cooperation with [Dr. Frederike Zufall](https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Frederike_Zufall), try to operationalize the German Criminal Code § 130 into an NLP task.